Baetis lutheri has a wide distribution in the West Palearctic (
Bauernfeind and Soldan 2012
) but recent molecular analysis has shown that it may constitute a complex of closely related species ( Tenchini et al. 2018 ). Koch (1988) reported it from Lebanon and Syria, but these reports may refer to B. golanensis . Baetis golanensis also corresponds to the undescribed " Baetis A12" mentioned by Samocha, also from Israel (1972: 44, pls XVIII-XIX ).
